This paper deals with machine learning algorithms for emotional speech recognition, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), which specifically deals with audio and speech processing. The paper also involves natural language processing, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of deep learning techniques and generative adversarial networks suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the use of multitask learning, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
